    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Fava</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Italy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23,
                                1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received October 25.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>:</p>
                <p>I have the honor to inform your excellency that as I was leaving from
                            Chicago I received yesterday from his excellency the minister of foreign
                            affairs of Italy the following telegram: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>, <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1892</hi>.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">To the <hi rend="smallcaps">Italian
                                        Minister</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>Yesterday at La Spezia the American flag was saluted with
                                    twenty-one guns.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brin.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fava.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
